7^2 = 49, \quad 7^4 = (7^2)^2 = 49^2 = 2401 \equiv 1 \pmod{100}, \quad 7^8 = (7^4)^2 \equiv 1^2 = 1 \pmod{100}, \quad 7^{10} = 7^8 \cdot 7^2 \equiv 1 \cdot 49 = 49 \pmod{100}
\] Therefore, the remainder when \(7^{2010}\) is divided by 100 is 49. </think> <answer> 49 </answer>
